<span id="freeTextContainer6523180580743818118">Endlessly fascinating, but what a painful experience it is to read this book. It epitomises Balzac&apos;s greatest themes: the provincial trying to make good in Paris, the wreckage in the wake of unbridled ambition, and the complexity and brutality of machinations that few come to understand.</span>
  <span id="freeText6523180580743818118" style="display:none">Endlessly fascinating, but what a painful experience it is to read this book. It epitomises Balzac's greatest themes: the provincial trying to make good in Paris, the wreckage in the wake of unbridled ambition, and the complexity and brutality of machinations that few come to understand.</span>
