        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer363123307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5358368876968767449">Lost Illusions (Illusions Perdues) is a trilogy of three novels which should be read in order:<br/>The Two Poets (Les Deux Poetes)<br/>A Distinguished Provincial at Paris/A Great Man of the Provinces in Paris (Un Grand homme de province a Paris)<br/>Eve and David/The Trials of the Inventor (Le Souffrances de l&apos;inventeur)<br/><br/>The story continues in a fourth novel:<br/>Scenes from a Courtesan&apos;s Life/A Harlot High and Low (Splendeurs et Miseres des Courtisanes)<br/><br/>See the individual titles for more information.</span>
  <span id="freeText5358368876968767449" style="display:none">Lost Illusions (Illusions Perdues) is a trilogy of three novels which should be read in order:<br />The Two Poets (Les Deux Poetes)<br />A Distinguished Provincial at Paris/A Great Man of the Provinces in Paris (Un Grand homme de province a Paris)<br />Eve and David/The Trials of the Inventor (Le Souffrances de l'inventeur)<br /><br />The story continues in a fourth novel:<br />Scenes from a Courtesan's Life/A Harlot High and Low (Splendeurs et Miseres des Courtisanes)<br /><br />See the individual titles for more information.</span>
